    <item>
      <title>Hierarchical Trajectory Planning of Floating-Base Multi-Link Robot for Maneuvering in Confined Environments</title>
      <link>https://yichengchen.com/publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yichengchen.com/publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;iframe src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/GOcorcrLGb4&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; allowfullscreen title=&#34;YouTube Video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/system_overview_hu939d389b537fb01a13383b64325c5fe4_555600_5a05333362797fcb76558eb39f3510a5.webp 400w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/system_overview_hu939d389b537fb01a13383b64325c5fe4_555600_306d01be6f7d445dbd3eb219d43f2d13.webp 760w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/system_overview_hu939d389b537fb01a13383b64325c5fe4_555600_1200x1200_fit_q100_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/system_overview_hu939d389b537fb01a13383b64325c5fe4_555600_5a05333362797fcb76558eb39f3510a5.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;296&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System overview.&lt;/strong&gt; The hierarchical trajectory planning framework decomposes the planning problem into independently solvable segments by introducing global anchor states, enabling parallel local planning. With clamped B-spline trajectory parameterization, continuity between adjacent segments is inherently maintained in the overall trajectory. Each segment is optimized in parallel with fully differential objective and constraint functions. The optimized local segments are directly concatenated in sequence to produce the final trajectory.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/sim_example_hua91acbc619f7c0f3ac3c1eac1911c69e_1586239_6049be9c4fab02db6d2d8d862f2749d6.webp 400w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/sim_example_hua91acbc619f7c0f3ac3c1eac1911c69e_1586239_fe304c2de699b16570e34fbf861e679e.webp 760w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/sim_example_hua91acbc619f7c0f3ac3c1eac1911c69e_1586239_1200x1200_fit_q100_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/sim_example_hua91acbc619f7c0f3ac3c1eac1911c69e_1586239_6049be9c4fab02db6d2d8d862f2749d6.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;387&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simulation of a floating-base multi-link robot navigating through a confined environment with narrow passages.&lt;/strong&gt; (a) Illustration of the global anchor states, each specifying a complete robot configuration, with the global initial and target states serving as the first and last global anchor states. There were seven anchor states in total. (b) Snapshots of the robot along the flight trajectory. (c) Changing histories of the objective function for all six trajectory segments, where red dots mark the minimum values of the objective. (d) Desired trajectories of the root link position and yaw angle (top) and the joint angles (bottom), with background shading indicating different planning segments.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/real_world_pcl_test_hucfbc91c5b776c0a47bdf221c7318f9d1_2295910_f88f192035a68f36c06a13083a1e132c.webp 400w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/real_world_pcl_test_hucfbc91c5b776c0a47bdf221c7318f9d1_2295910_c1e3f10d1c4f5eea4a54fac6e8c785d0.webp 760w,
               /publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/real_world_pcl_test_hucfbc91c5b776c0a47bdf221c7318f9d1_2295910_1200x1200_fit_q100_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/hierarchical-multi-link-planner/figures/real_world_pcl_test_hucfbc91c5b776c0a47bdf221c7318f9d1_2295910_f88f192035a68f36c06a13083a1e132c.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;233&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evaluation with real-world point clouds under environment changes.&lt;/strong&gt; A handheld Livox Mid-360 LiDAR was used to capture the scene, and FAST-LIO was used to reconstruct two registered point clouds before and after the obstacles were rearranged. (a) Experimental scene. (b) Point cloud of the initial scene. (c) Online volumetric occupancy map reconstructed from (b) and used for the initial plan. (d) Updated occupancy map after switching the input to the second point cloud, where the original passage was blocked (red boxes). (e) Execution snapshots in Gazebo (time was measured from the onset of motion): the robot started with the initial plan, the map update blocked the original passage at t = 17 s, replanning produced a new feasible trajectory at t = 19 s, and the robot switched to it and continued to the goal.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Learning to Initialize Trajectory Optimization for Vision-Based Autonomous Flight in Unknown Environments</title>
      <link>https://yichengchen.com/publication/neo-planner/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yichengchen.com/publication/neo-planner/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34;
           src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/neo-planner/figures/sim.gif&#34;
           loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of neural network predicted trajectories and corresponding optimized results.&lt;/strong&gt; The dashed lines with blue spherical markers represent neural network predictions, while solid lines with green spherical markers denote optimized trajectories. The network usually outputs near-optimal trajectories.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34;
           src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/neo-planner/figures/exp.gif&#34;
           loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A real-world demonstration of fully autonomous flight using the proposed Neural-Enhanced Trajectory Planner (NEO-Planner).&lt;/strong&gt; The drone has no prior knowledge of the environment, and the entire software stack runs onboard in real-time.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /publication/neo-planner/figures/system_overview_hu68ede0c8efa6992d669b528cff1811e8_921262_05173e154014c1c8281487f98a90fd43.webp 400w,
               /publication/neo-planner/figures/system_overview_hu68ede0c8efa6992d669b528cff1811e8_921262_f69cd4cf29f74076a8b1ecd72aaff211.webp 760w,
               /publication/neo-planner/figures/system_overview_hu68ede0c8efa6992d669b528cff1811e8_921262_1200x1200_fit_q100_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://yichengchen.com/publication/neo-planner/figures/system_overview_hu68ede0c8efa6992d669b528cff1811e8_921262_05173e154014c1c8281487f98a90fd43.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;322&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;small style=&#34;margin-top: -25px; display: block; line-height: 1.5;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System overview.&lt;/strong&gt; The NEO-Planner leverages a neural network to generate high-quality initial trajectories from onboard observations and subsequently conducts spatial-temporal optimization on the neural network&amp;rsquo;s output. The NN-Planner is trained using supervised learning, with training cases provided by an expert planner based on a standard mapping-planning-control stack.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Aeriva: A Mini Autonomous Quadrotor Platform</title>
      <link>https://yichengchen.com/project/aeriva/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Aug 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yichengchen.com/project/aeriva/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aeriva&lt;/strong&gt; - This name is a combination of &amp;ldquo;aero&amp;rdquo; (meaning air) and &amp;ldquo;diva&amp;rdquo; (suggesting a stylish and confident personality).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In March 2023, I began to design, assemble, and test this drone from scratch. So far, four drones of this type have been made and used in various scientific research and competitions in my lab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agile and safe&lt;/strong&gt;: Aeriva is built upon a 3.5-inch cinewhoop frame with Kakute H7 mini flight controller, making it exceptionally agile, compact and safe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High computing performance&lt;/strong&gt;: Aeriva is equipped with NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX, facilitating it with strong onboard computing capabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;specifications&#34;&gt;Specifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Component&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Specs&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Computer&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Camera&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Intel RealSense D435&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Stack&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Kakute H7 mini + Tekko32 F4 4in1 mini 45A ESC&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Dimension&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;152mm motor-to-motor&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Motors&lt;/td&gt;
